topic.title: SPI Single Bit ECC Command

body.p: The SPI Single Bit ECC Command provides a way to monitor the single bit ECC error count for flashes. It contains 5 sub-commands to monitor single bit ecc rate for specified flashes. However, these commands can be used in non-ecc mode, which makes no sense. Since the single bit ecc error count won't be increased in non-ecc mode. To get the correct error count, make sure the specified flash has the right ecc value in itself before monitoring. Users can flash an image data with ecc into the specified flash to make it. (see delete - Manufacturing Flash Image Generation)

MRPC SPI Single Bit ECC Sub-Command(1) Input Data

section.p: Set the single bit ecc error reporting threshold for specified SPI flash.
This field specifies the SPI Port ID.
This field specifies the threshold value, which is 32-bits unsigned integer.

When the increment of a single bit ecc error count hits the threshold every time interval, UART will print the error count out. The time interval is 1 second by default. If threshold is 0, UART would not print any ecc error count out. That is, the single bit ecc error reporting for the specified flash is disabled. And the time interval is able to be set by ema_poll_period_set() of ema_api.h in PSX SDK.

note.p: There is no output data for this sub-command.

topic.title: MRPC SPI Single Bit ECC Command - Example

body.p: Follow these steps to monitor the single bit ecc error of SPI Port 0:

ol.li:
Enable Interrupt.
Write address 0x000 with data: 0x10000
Write address 0x800 with data: 0x10020
Read address 0x808 for 1 DWORD data : MRPC Command Return value

Set Threshold to 128.
Write address 0x000 with data: 0x0001 0x0080
Write address 0x800 with data: 0x10020

Get Configure Data.
Write address 0x000 with data: 0x0004
Write address 0x800 with data: 0x10020
Read address 0x400 for 2 DWORD data : interrupt status, threshold

Read Count .
Write address 0x000 with data: 0x0003
Write address 0x800 with data: 0x10020
Read address 0x400 for 1 DWORD data : error count

Clear Count.
Write address 0x000 with data: 0x0002
Write address 0x800 with data: 0x10020
